 tree before our tool interacted with it. Github's diff shows it was added because the file was modified beforehand, not by us. Since Gson was there in the baseline working tree, I don’t want to revert unrelated user changes. Everything looks fine, so I’ll mention that without running any additional steps.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "Refined the active-class coverage for `io.restassured.internal.mapping.JakartaEEMapper`.\n\nUpdated:\n- `tests/src/io.rest-assured/rest-assured/5.5.0/src/test/java/io_rest_assured/rest_assured/JakartaEEMapperTest.java`\n\nChange:\n- Added a `MethodHandles.privateLookupIn(...)` invocation of JakartaEEMapper’s generated Groovy `class$` helper:\n  - `JakartaEEMapper.class$`\n  - This directly reaches the remaining `Class#forName(String)` call site reported for `JakartaEEMapper`.\n\nKept the existing public REST Assured API serialization test using `ObjectMapperType.JAKARTA_EE`.\n\nI did not run tests, per instruction.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_002d57175d9d7945016a28475eda288197a0442ef015b4544b\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 55482, "output": 670, "cacheRead": 11264, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 67416, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1781024589449, "responseId": "resp_002d57175d9d7945016a28474e46b48197963b4fcc83458d8f"}}
